_L = R1 × R2, or X_L² = R1 × R2. This confirms consistency between the given conditions. P = I² (R₁ + R₂) = U² / (R₁ + R₂). Substitute the values: P = 110² / (25 + 60) = 142.35 W\n\nEXPLANATION:\nTo solve this, Identify the impedance of each segment. Segment AM has impedance Z_AM = R1 - jX_C, and segment MB has impedance Z_MB = R2 + jX_L. The total circuit impedance is Z_AB = Z_AM + Z_MB. After computing, the result is 142.35 W.\n\nANSWER: 142.35 W"}]}
