 frequency. Substitute the expression from Step 3 into the result from\n- Step 2: Z_L = (30 × 2) / 3 = 20 Ω\n\nEXPLANATION:\nTo solve this, Determine the source voltage (U) using the resonance condition. At the resonant frequency (f = 50 Hz), the total impedance of the circuit is equal to the resistance R because the reactances cancel each other out (Z_L = Z_C). U = I × R = 1 × 40 = 40 V. After computing, the result is 20 Ω.\n\nANSWER: 20 Ω"}]}
